    &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;</code></pre>

	</section>

	<section id="striped-table">

		<h3>Striped Table</h3>
		<p>Include the <code>table-striped</code> @@mixin to your table style, or add class <code>striped</code> to the table markup. This adds alternating striped lines to the target table.</p>

		<div class="example">

			<table class="striped">

				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>#</th>
						<th>Team</th>
						<th>Division</th>
						<th>Record</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>

				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>1</td>
						<td>Chicago</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>10-6</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>2</td>
						<td>Green Bay</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>9-7</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>3</td>
						<td>Detroit</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>8-8</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>

			</table>

		</div>

		<pre><code class="language-css">table {
   @@include table-striped;
}</code></pre>

	</section>

	<section id="bordered-table">

		<h3>Bordered Table</h3>
		<p>Include the <code>table-bordered</code> @@mixin to your table style, or add class <code>bordered</code> to the table markup. This adds borders to the target table.</p>

		<div class="example">

			<table class="bordered">

				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>#</th>
						<th>Team</th>
						<th>Division</th>
						<th>Record</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>

				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>1</td>
						<td>Chicago</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>10-6</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>2</td>
						<td>Green Bay</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>9-7</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>3</td>
						<td>Detroit</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>8-8</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>

			</table>
		
		</div>

		<pre><code class="language-css">table {
   @@include table-bordered;
}</code></pre>

	</section>

	<section id="padded-table">

		<h3>Padded Table</h3>
		<p>Include the <code>table-padded</code> @@mixin to your table style, or add class <code>padded</code> to the table markup. This adds extra padding to the target table's cells.</p>

		<div class="example">

			<table class="padded">

				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>#</th>
						<th>Team</th>
						<th>Division</th>
						<th>Record</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>

				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>1</td>
						<td>Chicago</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>10-6</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>2</td>
						<td>Green Bay</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>9-7</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>3</td>
						<td>Detroit</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>8-8</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>

			</table>

			<p><small>Note: Padded tables with even numbers of rows (including header) will fit with the vertical rhythm, while odd numbers will be half a line off.</small></p>

		</div>

		<pre><code class="language-css">table {
   @@include table-padded;
}</code></pre>

	</section>

	<section id="striped-bordered-padded-table">

		<h3>Striped, Bordered, & Padded Table</h3>
		<p>Include the <code>table-striped</code>, <code>table-bordered</code>, or <code>table-padded</code> @@mixins to your table styles, or add the corresponding classes to the table markup. These can be added in any combination to customize the look of your tables.</p>

		<div class="example">

			<table class="striped bordered padded">

				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>#</th>
						<th>Team</th>
						<th>Division</th>
						<th>Record</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>

				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>1</td>
						<td>Chicago</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>10-6</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>2</td>
						<td>Green Bay</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>9-7</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>3</td>
						<td>Detroit</td>
						<td>North</td>
						<td>8-8</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>

			</table>

			<p><small>Note: Padded tables with even numbers of rows (including header) will fit with the vertical rhythm, while odd numbers will be half a line off.</small></p>

		</div>

		<pre><code class="language-css">table {
   @@include table-striped;
   @@include table-bordered;
   @@include table-padded;
}</code></pre>

	</section>

</section>